See change log https://github.com/MenoData/Time4J/blob/level6/CHANGELOG.md

This is the last version of level-6-branch (for Java 6+7) unless newer tzdb-versions with syntactical changes might require a new one. Wide parts of this release are identical to Time4A.

name: New islamic calendar
body:
This version is a backport of v4.3-release for the version line 3.x, see also:

https://github.com/MenoData/Time4J/releases/tag/v4.3

Furthermore: The android-module has been removed in favour of a new project named Time4A.

name: New islamic calendar
body:
**New Features**
- Create an experimental version of Umalqura calendar [#313]
- Start-of-day-feature, relevant for current date in islamic calendar [#323]
- New pattern type for generic date chronologies [#324]
- New transformation methods for calendrical objects [#318]

**Deprecations**
- Interface `ExtZoneProvider` no longer used

**Incompatibilities**
- Narrow value-type of BasicElement to Comparable [#321]
